Importing & cleaning data

Reads in packages and cleans data

library(xlsx)
library(tidyverse)
library(hrbrthemes)
library(downloadthis) # Don't need this, it's for my formatting of this page



hrbrthemes::import_roboto_condensed()
color4 <- c("indeterminate" = "darkgrey", 
           "negative" = "#8B1E3F", 
           "positive" = "#13505B")



cabo <- read.csv ("CABOAERODATA.csv") |> 
  janitor::clean_names() |> 
  filter(indication != "") |> 
  mutate(indication = str_squish(indication)) |> 
  mutate(indication = gsub("Non-small Cell Lung Cancer", "NSCLC", indication), 
           indication = gsub(" Cancer$", "", indication),
           indication = str_squish(indication), 
           date = as.Date(year, "%m/%d/%Y"), 
            year = lubridate::year(date),
           result = tolower(result), 
           participants = as.numeric(gsub("," ,"", participants)), 
           id = row_number()) |> 
   # The following adds 30 days to dates that are overlapping on the timeline
  group_by(indication, phase) |> 
  arrange(date) |> 
  mutate(diff = date - lag(date)) |> 
  mutate(date = if_else(diff <= 30 & (!is.na(diff)), date + ddays(30), date)) |> 
  ungroup()

Figure 1.1

This is the closest to the example I could provide in R. I changed the shapes to be more slightly more intuitive (open circle = phase, closed circle = phase 3)

fig1.1 <- cabo |> 
  add_count(indication) |> 
  mutate(size_ = case_when(
      phase == "I"|  phase == "II" ~ 1,
      phase == "III" ~ 2 ,

    )) |> 
  mutate(size_ = size_ + as.numeric(participants)) |> 
  arrange(date) |> 
  group_by(year, indication) |> 
  mutate(order = row_number(), 
         order = year+ (1-(1*.9)/order)) |> 
  ungroup() |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = order, y = fct_reorder(indication, n), color = result,
               shape = phase, size = size_)) +
  geom_point( position = position_jitter(width =0, height =-0.02))  +

  scale_shape_manual(values = c("III" = "\u25CF", "II" = "\u25CE", "I" = "\u2B58", 
                                  family = "Arial Unicode MS",
                                  type = 'cairo'
                                  )) +

  scale_size_area(max_size = 18) +
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(2011, 2023), 
                     breaks = seq(2011, 2023, 1), 
                     position = "top") +
    scale_color_manual(values = color4, 
                       aesthetics = "color") +
  labs(y = "Indication", 
       x = "Year of publication") +
    theme_minimal(base_family = "Roboto Condensed" 
                  ) +
    geom_hline(yintercept=seq(.5, length(unique(cabo$indication))+1 , 1), 
             lwd=0.2, colour="grey", alpha = 0.2) +
    guides(size = F, 
         shape = guide_legend(override.aes = list(size = 5), 
                              title="Phase"), 
         color = guide_legend(override.aes = list(size = 5), 
                              title="Result")) +
    theme(panel.grid.major.y = element_blank(),
          panel.grid.minor.y = element_line(color = "black"),
          panel.grid.major.x = element_blank(),
          panel.grid.minor.x = element_blank(),
          legend.position = "bottom", 
          legend.box = "vertical", 
          #legend.text = element_text(margin = margin(0,0,0,-.05, "cm")), 
          legend.spacing = unit(0, 'cm'), 
          legend.box.spacing = unit(0, 'cm'),
          legend.box.just = "left"
          )

Figure 1.2

This one tried to seperate the phases more distinctly. has the size of each point as a categorized variable of # of participant.

levs2 <- cabo |> 
  count(indication, sort = T) |> 
  pull(indication)





phase_counter <- tibble(phase = rep(list(c("I", "II", "III")), length(levs2)), 
       indication = levs2) |> 
  unnest(phase)


phase_counter2 <-cabo |>
  count(indication, phase) |> 
  full_join(phase_counter, by = c("phase", "indication")) |> 
  # filter(indication == "Bone Metastasis") |> 
  mutate(hasPhase = ifelse(is.na(n), "n", "y"))


fake_phases <- phase_counter2 |> 
  select(-n) |> 
  mutate( dayssince = as.numeric((as.Date("01/01/2010",  "%m/%d/%Y")-(as.Date("01/01/2011",  "%m/%d/%Y")))), 
          result = "fake")



color5 <- c("indeterminate" = "darkgrey", 
           "negative" = "#8B1E3F", 
           "positive" = "#13505B")





cabo_form1 <- cabo |> 
  mutate(enddate = date + 360, 
           dayssince = as.numeric(date-(as.Date("01/01/2011",  "%m/%d/%Y")))) |> 
  bind_rows(fake_phases) |> 
  mutate(indication = factor(indication, levels = levs2), 
         phase = factor(phase, levels = rev(c("I", "II", "III")))) |> 
    arrange(dayssince) |> 
  group_by(indication, phase) |> 
  mutate(id = paste0(indication, "_p", phase, ".", id), 
         id2 = paste0(indication, "_p", phase), 
         id2 = factor(id2))  |> 
  ungroup() |> 
  mutate(size_ = cut_number(participants, n =5)) 




gridz  <- cbind(
bind_rows(rep(
list(tibble(line_start = as.numeric((as.Date("01/01/2011",  "%m/%d/%Y")-(as.Date("01/01/2011",  "%m/%d/%Y")))), 
                line_end = 4745)), nrow(phase_counter))), id2 = levels(cabo_form1$id2)) |> 
  mutate(indication = str_squish(gsub("_.*", "", id2)), 
         phase = gsub(".*_p", "", id2), 
         id2 = factor(id2, levels = levels(cabo_form1$id2)), 
         indication = factor(indication, levels = levels(cabo_form1$indication)))


phase_label <- function(x) {
  #return(gsub(".*_p", "", x))
  r1 <- gsub("III", "3", gsub(".*_p", "", x))
  
  r2 <- gsub("II", "2", r1)
  
  r3 <- gsub("I", "1", r2)
  
  r4 <- paste0("Phase ", r3)
  
  return(r4)
}



fig1.2 <- ggplot() +
    geom_segment(data = gridz, aes(y = id2, yend = id2, x = line_start, xend = line_end, linetype = phase), color = "grey") +
    geom_point(data = cabo_form1, aes(x = dayssince, y = id2, color = result, size = size_), shape = 21) +
    facet_wrap(~ indication, ncol = 1, scales = "free_y", strip.position =  "left") +
    scale_x_continuous(limits = c(0, 4745),
                        breaks = seq(0, 4745, 365), 
                         labels = seq(2011, 2024, 1), 
                         position = "top", 
                       expand = c(0,0)) +
    scale_y_discrete(#position = "right", 
                     labels = phase_label) +
    scale_linetype_manual(values = c("dotted", "dashed", "solid")) +
    scale_color_manual(values = color5, 
                       aesthetics = "color") +
  scale_size_manual(values =c(1,2,3,4,5)) +
    labs(
         x = "Time of publication") +
    theme_minimal(base_family = "Roboto Condensed") +
  guides(size = F, 
         linetype = F, 
         color = guide_legend(override.aes = list(size = 5), 
                              title="Result")) +
    theme(#axis.text.y = element_blank(), 
          axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45,  hjust = 0),
          axis.text.y = element_text(  size = 5, vjust = 0.5, hjust = 1),
          axis.title.y = element_blank(),
          panel.grid.major.x = element_blank(),
          panel.grid.minor.x = element_blank(),
          panel.grid.major.y = element_blank(),
          strip.text.y.left = element_text( angle = 360, hjust = 1), 
          strip.placement = "outside"
    )

Figure 1.3

This is the same as above but attempt to add participant size as number of dots. Bit misleading since someone could think that it portrays the length of study recruitment.

 simulated_dots2 <- cabo |> 
  mutate(enddate = date + 360, 
           dayssince = as.numeric(date-(as.Date("01/01/2011",  "%m/%d/%Y")))) |> 
  bind_rows(fake_phases) |> 
  arrange(dayssince) |> 
  group_by(indication, phase) |> 
  mutate(id = paste0(indication, "_p", phase, ".", id), 
         id2 = paste0(indication, "_p", phase), 
         id2 = factor(id2),
         indication = factor(indication))  |> 
   # filter(id == "Renal Cell Carcinoma_pII.4") |>
   filter(!is.na(participants)) |> 
   group_by(id) |> 
    #mutate(fake_data = list(rnorm(participants, dayssince, dayssince*0.05))) |> 
   #mutate(fake_data = list(rbeta(participants, 2, 9, 0))) |> 
     mutate(fake_data = list(abs(rnorm(participants, sd = participants*0.01)) * -1)) |> 
    unnest(fake_data) |> 
    mutate(fake_data = dayssince + (fake_data*100)) |> 
     select(-dayssince) |> 
   rename(dayssince =  fake_data)|> 
 mutate(dayssince = ifelse(dayssince < 0, dayssince * -1, dayssince))
   # mutate(dayssince = dayssince - (fake_data*participants))
